<h2 id="02-encrypting-the-current-time">02. Encrypting the current time</h2>

<p>The <code class="highlighter-rouge">date</code> command is used to display or modify the current date and time (see more detail about it at this link: Setting Date and Time in Linux).</p>

<p>The <code class="highlighter-rouge">md5sum</code> command generates an <code class="highlighter-rouge">MD5</code> encryption <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/what-is-and-how-to-generate-a-hash/">hash</a> and its stdout we send it to the awk command which will print only the first column (<code class="highlighter-rouge">$1</code>), since the second is a dash (<code class="highlighter-rouge">-</code>).</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">date</span> | <span class="nb">md5sum</span> | <span class="nb">awk</span> <span class="s1">'{print $1}'</span></code></pre></figure>

<hr />

