<h2 id="09-using-pwgen">09. Using pwgen</h2>

<p>Pwgen is a small GPL password generator that creates passwords that can be easily memorized by a human being.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Install it first, eg <code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo emerge -a pwgen</code></p>
</blockquote>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="c"># Usage examples</span>
pwgen <span class="nt">-s</span>
pwgen <span class="nt">-s</span> <span class="nt">-1</span>
pwgen <span class="nt">-s</span> <span class="nt">-1</span> 14
pwgen <span class="nt">-s</span> 10 5 <span class="nt">-1</span> <span class="nt">-y</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Read more: <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/pwgen/">https://sourceforge.net/projects/pwgen/</a></p>

