<h2 id="13-using-diceware">13. Using <code class="highlighter-rouge">diceware</code></h2>

<p>Diceware is a method for creating passwords and other cryptographic variables using common data as a hardware random number generator. For each word in the password, five rolls of the dice are required.</p>

<p>The numbers 1 through 6 that appear on the rollers are mounted as a five digit number, for example 43146. This number is used to search for a word in a word list. In the English list 43146 corresponds to munch. By generating multiple words in sequence, a long password can be constructed.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Install it first, eg <code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo apt install diceware</code></p>
</blockquote>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="c"># Usage examples</span>
diceware</code></pre></figure>

<p>Link: <a href="https://github.com/ulif/diceware">https://github.com/ulif/diceware</a></p>

